  "title": "Account Servicing Intern",
  "description": "<p>You have a bright and positive personality, loves food, travel and all things fun. Strives in a tight-knitted Team and motivating work environment. Most importantly, you want to attain achievements which you will be proud of.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<p>· Manage daily emails, timeline and assist in the implementation and execution of client servicing tasks.</p>\n<p>· Actively brainstorm and engage with the internal team to provide marketing and campaign ideas.</p>\n<p>· Manage accounts by ensuring brands’ objectives and timelines are met, overseeing creative development and video production and ensuring smooth delivery of deliverables.</p>\n<p>· Assist on creating proposals/media kits for incoming client campaigns by working with the internal team in developing content that meet client’s objectives.</p>\n<p>· Prepare campaign reports.</p>\n<p>· Cross sell and handle inbound sales.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<p>• Students from Media/Marketing/Communications or equivalent.</p>\n<p>• Meticulous and resilient.</p>\n<p>• Strong written and oral communication skills.</p>\n<p>• Good understanding of consumer trends on social media.</p>\n<p>• Strong understanding of social media platforms, especially TikTok and YouTube.</p>\n<p>• Passionate about new media and digital content, with strong interest in social media content creation.</p>\n<p>• Strong presentation, interpersonal, organizational skills.</p>\n<p>• Proactive &amp; hungry for results.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>-Min. 6 months (full time) onsite commitment</p>\n<p>-Opportunity to convert to permanent role</p>",
